		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hmmm.....mine looked pretty darn good - I'm wondering if the AV mod I did may effect it a little, since the pathway leading under the VRAM now has a much stronger signal.  Perhaps re-routing the signal coming out of the transistor to the modulator aome other way may elimininate more interference.  Actually, the VRAM was one of my original suspects, since some of my vs. arcade boards also have these lines, but only when certain video pages are being used.  I also noticed that if I run my Famicom off of the +5V supply of my NES (with the CPU &amp; PPU removed from the NES to reduce power consumption), the Famicom would get the lines, so the power supply may be contributing to the problem in some way.

		

