		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hey..
<br />
<br />like it or not, holes need to be cut, otherwise you have only video and no audio.  I never tried removing the current RF modulator, but it doesn't work (since video out pin in PPU is lifted).
<br />
<br />The video quality itself is identical to the front loader (I did an A/B comparison while both systems were running!).  I don't have a famicom toploader AV, so can't compare to it.
<br />
<br />As far as AC/DC converter is concerned, I'm not sure the problem is there.  Even if you use a DC input (which works!) the system still had the vertical lines.

		

